# Let git auto-detect text vs binary, then normalise text to LF on
# commit regardless of the contributor's platform. Checkouts still use
# the platform's native line endings (so Windows editors stay happy),
# but the repo on GitHub is LF-only — which is what GitHub renders from
# anyway, and what the dime.svg <text> elements expect.
* text=auto

# Explicitly tag what's text so git doesn't have to guess.
*.md    text
*.svg   text
*.txt   text

# Images stay binary.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.ico   binary
